Heat the olive oil in a frying pan, add the chorizo and pan fry for 2-3 minutes each side with a pinch of paprika.Place the sun-dried tomatoes, the two tablespoons of oil from the jar and garlic into a mini-blender with a squeeze of lemon juice and blend to a coarse paste.To serve, place a slice of griddled bread onto a serving plate, top with the chorizo sausage. Pour the sun-dried tomato dressing on top and then scatter with chopped parsley.